# Security Hardening Guide

ForgeScript includes comprehensive security features to protect participant data and ensure experiment integrity.

## Overview

The security hardening system includes:
- Content Security Policy (CSP) enforcement
- Dependency vulnerability scanning
- Consent data encryption
- Rate limiting and payload validation
- Automated security scanning in CI/CD

## Content Security Policy (CSP)

### Basic Usage

```typescript
import { ContentSecurityPolicy } from '@psyforge/forgescript/security';

// Get CSP instance
const csp = ContentSecurityPolicy.getInstance();

// Apply default CSP to document
csp.applyToDocument();

// Create secure inline scripts
const script = csp.createInlineScript(`
  console.log('This script has a valid nonce');
`);
document.head.appendChild(script);
```

### Custom CSP Configuration

```typescript
csp.configure({
  reportOnly: true, // Test mode
  directives: {
    'img-src': ["'self'", 'https://cdn.example.com'],
    'connect-src': ["'self'", 'https://api.example.com'],
  },
  reportUri: 'https://example.com/csp-report',
});
```

### Server Middleware

```typescript
import { cspMiddleware } from '@psyforge/forgescript/security';
import express from 'express';

const app = express();

// Apply CSP middleware
app.use(cspMiddleware({
  reportOnly: false,
  strictDynamic: true,
}));

// Use nonce in templates
app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.render('index', { 
    cspNonce: res.locals.cspNonce 
  });
});
```

## Dependency Security Scanning

### Automated Scanning

```bash
# Run dependency audit
npm run security:audit

# Check with specific threshold
npm run security:check

# Generate HTML report
npm run security:report
```

### Programmatic Usage

```typescript
import { DependencyAuditor } from '@psyforge/forgescript/security';

const auditor = new DependencyAuditor();

// Run audit
const result = await auditor.audit({
  includeDev: false,
  failOn: 'high',
  format: 'html',
  outputPath: './security-report.html',
});

console.log(`Found ${result.summary.total} vulnerabilities`);
console.log(`Critical: ${result.summary.critical}`);
console.log(`High: ${result.summary.high}`);
```

### Code Pattern Scanning

```typescript
// Check for dangerous patterns
const warnings = await auditor.checkCodePatterns([
  './src/experiment.ts',
  './src/stimuli.ts',
]);

warnings.forEach(warning => {
  console.warn(warning);
});
```

## Consent Data Encryption

### Encrypting Consent

```typescript
import { 
  ConsentDataEncryption,
  ConsentData 
} from '@psyforge/forgescript/security';

const encryption = new ConsentDataEncryption();

// Create consent data
const consent: ConsentData = {
  participantId: 'P12345',
  timestamp: new Date(),
  consentType: 'informed_consent',
  granted: true,
  details: {
    studyId: 'STUDY001',
    studyTitle: 'Visual Perception Study',
    researcherName: 'Dr. Smith',
    institutionName: 'Research University',
    ethicsApprovalNumber: 'ETH-2024-001',
    dataRetentionPeriod: '5 years',
    withdrawalMethod: 'Email researcher@example.com',
  },
  signature: 'Digital signature data',
};

// Encrypt with password
const encrypted = await encryption.encryptConsent(
  consent,
  'strong-password-from-key-management'
);

// Store encrypted consent
await consentStorage.store(encrypted);
```

### Decrypting Consent

```typescript
// Retrieve and decrypt
const encrypted = await consentStorage.retrieve(participantId, studyId);
const consent = await encryption.decryptConsent(
  encrypted,
  'strong-password-from-key-management'
);

// Validate consent is still valid
if (encryption.isConsentValid(consent, 365)) {
  console.log('Consent is valid');
}
```

### Consent Withdrawal

```typescript
// Create withdrawal record
const withdrawal = await encryption.createWithdrawalRecord(
  participantId,
  studyId,
  'Participant requested data deletion'
);

// Store withdrawal and delete original consent
await consentStorage.store(withdrawal);
await consentStorage.delete(participantId, studyId);
```

## Rate Limiting

### Basic Rate Limiting

```typescript
import { RateLimiter, RateLimitPresets } from '@psyforge/forgescript/security';

// Create rate limiter with preset
const limiter = new RateLimiter(RateLimitPresets.normal);

// Check if request should be allowed
const context = { 
  ip: request.ip,
  sessionId: request.sessionId 
};

if (await limiter.checkLimit(context)) {
  // Process request
} else {
  // Return 429 Too Many Requests
}
```

### API Endpoint Protection

```typescript
import { 
  APIRateLimiter, 
  PayloadLimitPresets 
} from '@psyforge/forgescript/security';

// Create API rate limiter
const apiLimiter = new APIRateLimiter(PayloadLimitPresets.normal);

// Configure endpoints
apiLimiter.addEndpoint('/api/submit-data', {
  maxRequests: 10,
  windowMs: 60 * 1000, // 1 minute
});

apiLimiter.addEndpoint('/api/download-results', {
  maxRequests: 5,
  windowMs: 5 * 60 * 1000, // 5 minutes
});

// Express middleware
app.use('/api/*', createRateLimitMiddleware(
  req.path,
  apiLimiter
